column3: "I felt that it was best, giving the most options to move "
"I found a way that I would win regardless what o does on the 4th round"

"I looked for moves which forced O to respond in one way to prevent an immediate win by me.  Ultimately setting up a 3 in a row with space at both ends for a win.  Made sure O didn't get into a position where I had to stop O from winning instead of working on my plan."
"I forced O by making 3 x's every turn. On the third move I made 3 x's with blanks at both blanks which makes O impossible to prevent losing."
"Trial and error.  I went through as many different possibilities as I could, making sure that O would not win before X and making sure X would have a sure win in 4 moves."
"tried to place the x where i could win 2 ways "

"I simply looked for the best space as far as what would cluster more X's together and if that didn't work when playing out I went to the next one until I was sure it forced O to play a certain way that would make X victorious."
"try to make more than one way to win"
"I picked a position that would give me the opportunity to set up 3 in a row on the next turn no matter where blue placed."
"I tried my best but it was really hard with the time counting down."
"I tried every combination of moves where each side was maximizing their play"
"I tried to keep O from solving it first while trying to get it."
"I just thought it out in my head."

"I used the placement of the X's that were already there and tried thinking in terms of both X and O. I navigated in a way that allowed X to have more than one way to win, even if O tried to cut X off every time."
"Analyze the board then place the x where it minimizes the opponent's options"
"I wanted to set up the board so that there would be 2 places to win from based on the pieces currently on the board."
"Honestly, was just a guess.  I didn't think I'd get any correct answer, and it seemed like the right thing to maximize my chances of winning."

"I fiddled a bit and saw that one particular space - C3 - would allow X to set up a line of 3 in several ways. O can block once in this time, but it is unable to stop X's expansion after this point. "
"I played out the scenario a few times and noticed that every time X was able to win."
"By getting the x in the mddle, it's easy to have the borders even if o is playing well."
"I tried to find a way where I would set myself up for O to have to choose one or the other."
"I had to figure out where o would make an unwinnable situation like the tutorial demonstrated. Then I had to try and find a way for x to make that similar situation appear."
"I tried to create the option of placing an X in two different spots to ensure a win.  Therefore, even if O blocks one of my winning spots, I would still have the other winning spot."
"Make plays that forced O to block and build off X's strategy from there."
"I started off to the side and worked my way across letting o go the other way"
"I set up a three-way trap that would make O's choices irrelevant."
"i saw the solution that i thought would result in x winning in a maximum of 4 moves and replayed it twice using o's best moves and it worked out that no matter what o did, x would win"

"I placed my x's on the board and played out the scenario trying to get three x's in a row with both ends open.  I tried to pick spaces that O would be forced to block and that would allow me to get the three in a row with both ends open."
"I tried a few spots until I found one that worked."
"I used what I learned during the quiz practice to find the winning move. I set up a situation where no matter where my opponent places their O I am able to place an x for the win."
"just clicked around and saw the outcomes"
"I made three x's in a row, so that o had to go where I wanted it to."
"I made moves that ensured I could win in a few different ways"
"I went for an area where x could get 4 in a row"

"I found the first move that would give me 3 consecutive Xs, and force O to block. Then proceded to continue the process until I had 3 X in a row with open spaces on both sides so O was guaranteed to lose in 2 moves."

"I tried to force the O player to react to the X player's moves, while continuously placing pressure upon the O player, with the ultimate goal of creating an open ended 3 in a row for the X player, which would ensure the win."
"I tried to cut off 0's opportunity to make 4 places in a row. Then I tried to place my X in a spot that would require O to block and I could still go the other way."
"I tried to find the first move that would give the most options for X to win, considering the moves that O would most likely make."
"I looked for positions where X could win in multiple ways. "
